cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper describes an algorithm for approximating data by a mixture of flats, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves clustering and optimization, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance using synthetic and real data, which falls under the category of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
